part 1

main filter function

photo = function(matric,k){
  n=dim(matric)[1]
  m=dim(matric)[2]
  matric.pad= matrix(0, n+2*k, m+2*k)
  matric.pad[(k+1):(n+k), (k+1):(m+k)] <- matric
  n.pad=n+2*k
  m.pad=m+2*k
  matric.avg<- matrix(0, n.pad, m.pad)
  for(x in (k+1):(n+k)){
       for(y in (k+1):(m+k)){
         total=sum(matric.pad[(x-k):(x+k),(y-k):(y+k)])
         matric.avg[x,y]=(total/((2*k+1)*(2*k+1)))
            }
      }
  shrink.pad= matric.avg[(k+1):(n+k), (k+1):(m+k)]
  return(shrink.pad)
}

part 2

sd filter function

photo_sd = function(matric,k){
  n=dim(matric)[1]
  m=dim(matric)[2]
  matric.pad= matrix(0, n+2*k, m+2*k)
  matric.pad[(k+1):(n+k), (k+1):(m+k)] <- matric
  n.pad=n+2*k
  m.pad=m+2*k
  matric.sd<- matrix(0, n.pad, m.pad)
  for(x in (k+1):(n+k)){
       for(y in (k+1):(m+k)){
         matric.avg=sum(matric.pad[(x-k):(x+k),(y-k):(y+k)])/((2*k+1)*(2*k+1))
         matric.sd[x,y]= sqrt((matric.pad[x,y] - matric.avg)^2/((2*k+1)*(2*k+1)))
            }
      }
  shrink.pad= matric.sd[(k+1):(n+k), (k+1):(m+k)]
  return(shrink.pad)
}

get the edge of van gogh

rsd=photo_sd(g.van_gogh,1)
l=round(length(rsd)*0.95)

Answer for question 1

The edging detection by red channel is showing the waving feature of the painting. we can see there is more color change in the bird are and the land area, reletively less color change in the sky.

Answer for question 2

We can see the road distribution of madison, and also see the lake area because there is relatively less color change.
